One hundred years after the Russian Revolution and 50 years after the revolutionary general strike in France in 1968, many on the left question whether the working class has a central role in changing society.
As the accompanying piece explains, contrary to those who say that globalization or automation have eliminated the American working class, it remains without doubt the majority of society.
A Grim FutureThere is massive anger at social inequality and the social crisis which faces large sections of the working class.
But until recently, working class revolt was only expressed in a partial way and largely on the electoral plane.
This will truly be the emergence of a working class “for itself” in America.